exportLetterContent.weHaveReceivedNotificationFrom: We have received a notification from
exportLetterContent.advisingUsToTerminateItsQuikcardHealthSp: advising us to terminate its Quikcard Health Spending Account effective
exportLetterContent.weHaveSentALetterPara: We have sent a letter to the Plan Administrator outlining the process for employees to submit outstanding claims and settlement of the final balance on the plan account.

planAdminLetterContent.weHaveReceivedNotificationFrom: We have received a notification from
planAdminLetterContent.advisingUsToTerminateItsQuikcardHealthSp: advising us to terminate its Quikcard Health Spending Account effective
planAdminLetterContent.weAreSorry: We are sorry to lose you as a Quikcard client.  This notification provides some information about the termination process.
planAdminLetterContent.yourEmployeesMayPara: Your employees may have claims incurred prior to the Termination Date that they have not yet submitted to the Quikcard Plan. These claims may be submitted for
planAdminLetterContent.daysPastTheTerminationDate: days past the Termination Date for reimbursement. This is called the runout period.
planAdminLetterContent.preAuthorizedMonthlyPara: Pre-authorized monthly payments will no longer be automatically withdrawn from your bank account.  Your plan will have no credit limit during the runout period, so you may receive a request for additional funding for us to be able to release approved claims. To avoid this, you may wish to provide an additional payment and any amount remaining will be refunded at the end of the runout period.
planAdminLetterContent.atTheConclusionPara: At the conclusion of the runout period, Quikcard will review your account for any pending claims to be resolved. Pending claims may arise if there are valid claims to be paid, but there is not sufficient funding in your Quikcard account to cover the cost. Pending claims may also arise if you have the Extra Benefits provision in your plan design.  We will contact you if there are pending claims at that time.
planAdminLetterContent.onceAnyPendingPara: Once any pending claims are resolved, Quikcard will provide you with a final statement of the Quikcard account balance. If there is a positive balance in the account, Quikcard will issue a refund payment on that date. If there is a balance owing to Quikcard, the settlement payment from you is due within 30 days.
planAdminLetterContent.pleaseContactOurAdmin: Please contact our Administration team at 1-800-232-1997 or
planAdminLetterContent.onceAgainPara: Once again, we are sorry to lose you as a Quikcard client and we hope that you will consider returning if your circumstances change.

planAdminSurplusLetterContent.dayRunoutPeriodForClaims: day runout period for claims submission has concluded. The attached statement shows the final balance of your Quikcard account.
